method.description:
				Concatenates the page's current transformation matrix and specified matrix.
				For example, if you want to rotate the coordinate system of the page by 45 degrees, use concat() as follows.
				[codeblock]float rad1 = 45 / 180 * 3.141592;
				page.concat(Transform2D(Vector2(cos(rad1), sin(rad1)), Vector2(-sin(rad1), cos(rad1)), Vector2(220, 350));[/codeblock]
				To change the coordinate system of the page to 300 dpi, use concat() as follows.
				[codeblock]concat(Transform2D(Vector2(72.0f / 300.0f, 0), Vector2(0, 72.0f / 300.0f), Vector2(0, 0));[/codeblock]
				Invoke g_save() before concat(). Then the change by concat() can be restored by invoking g_restore().
				[codeblock]// save the current graphics states
  			page.g_save(page);
				// concatenate the transformation matrix */
				page.concat(Transform2D(Vector2(72.0f / 300.0f, 0), Vector2(0, 72.0f / 300.0f), Vector2(0, 0));
				// show text on the translated coordinates
				page.begin_text();
				page.move_text_pos(50, 100);
				page.show_text("Text on the translated coordinates");
				page.end_text();
				// restore the graphics states
				page.g_restore();[/codeblock]
